How to Enable Cookies

To enable cookies, follow the instructions below for the browser version you are using.

Mozilla Firefox 2.0+
  • Go to the Tools menu.
  • Select Options.
  • Select the Privacy icon in the panel.
  • Check the box corresponding to Accept cookies from sites.
  • Select OK to save changes.
Apple Safari 5.0+
  • From the Safari menu, select Preferences.
  • From the Privacy dialog box, for Block Cookies, select Never.
  • Select Close.
Microsoft Internet Explorer 6.0+
  • Select Internet Options from the Tools menu.
  • Select the Privacy tab.
  • Select the Default button (or manually slide the bar down to Medium) under Settings.
  • Select OK.
In the top-right corner of Chrome, click the Chrome menu > Settings.
At the bottom of the page, click Show advanced settings.
In the "Privacy" section, click the Content settings button.
In the "Cookies" section, enable Allow local data to be set (recommended).
